d target Java 8. I want to make sure the tests are organized logically to ensure comprehensive coverage.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating Java configurations**\\\\n\\\\nI'm looking at restoring the Java version and deciding if it's okay to add \\\\\\\"--add-opens\\\\\\\" in build.gradle. I wonder if I could skip it by not invoking setAccessible, but if I don't add it, I encounter throws that leave certain lines uncovered. So, I'll need to add it. But when running a native image, those arguments become irrelevant. I'm considering custom ClassLoader support, catching any UnsupportedFeatureError, and ensuring proper resource reading from CleanUtil path. I'll use readAllBytes for reading bytes, but I hope the parent exposes the class resource!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Implementing loadClass method**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering implementing a synchronized loadClass method. If the class name isn't CLEAN_UTIL_CLASS_NAME, I'll return the super version. I need to find a loaded class or load it if it isn't already loaded. If I resolve, I'll call resolveClass. For finding classes, if it's only for the target, I’ll use getParent().getResourceAsStream for loading bytes. But what if the parent is null? It’ll throw an IOException. I also need to manage Method.invoke calls, which might add extra dynamic access call sites. I wonder how the TCK will track this!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_T541pIKNTgqa0G13gCpBmzxs|fc_01d3ce057da11f900169fe55d61da8819d90a7c65356365b56\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-hadoop/1.12.2/user-code-filter.json\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 664, \"output\": 912, \"cacheRead\": 23552, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 25128, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse