how to configure the default `test` to exclude legacy tests, using `legacyCleanUtilTest`. If I set it up so that `test.dependsOn legacyCleanUtilTest`, then running `./gradlew test` should properly execute both tasks. It seems that if a test task depends on another test task, it should work seamlessly. This way, I can manage the dependencies effectively!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Adjusting test configuration**\\\\n\\\\nI'm noticing that `tasks.withType(Test).configureEach` sets `jvmArgs` and might also set `useJUnitPlatform`, but only for test plugins. So, my custom setup should set those options too. If I create a custom Test, it will include all the classes, but only the tagged legacy ones. I think it would be good to place the tag string constant, so I’ll need to edit the build.gradle file and run tests accordingly.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_SnU8CQMdpfwBiCd8zMTmLodS|fc_01d3ce057da11f900169fe5788f8c8819db88a524e407699cb\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-hadoop/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_hadoop/CleanUtilTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_apache_parquet.parquet_hadoop;\\n\\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\\n\\nimport org.apache.parquet.hadoop.codec.CleanUtil;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Tag;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertDoesNotThrow;\\n\\npublic class CleanUtilTest {\\n    static final String LEGACY_CLEANER_TAG = \\\"legacy-clean-util\\\";\\n    private static final String JAVA_VERSION_PROPERTY = \\\"java.version\\\";\\n\\n    @Test\\n    @Tag(LEGACY_CLEANER_TAG)\\n    void cleanDirectBufferCanUseLegacyCleanerReflection() {\\n        String previousJavaVersion = System.getProperty(JAVA_VERSION_PROPERTY);\\n        try {\\n            System.setProperty(JAVA_VERSION_PROPERTY, \\\"1.8.0\\\");\\n            ByteBuffer directBuffer = newDirectBuffer();\\n\\n            assertDoesNotThrow(() -> CleanUtil.cleanDirectBuffer(directBuffer));\\n        } finally {\\n            restoreJavaVersion(previousJavaVersion);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void cleanDirectBufferAcceptsDirectByteBuffer() {\\n        ByteBuffer directBuffer = newDirectBuffer();\\n\\n        assertDoesNotThrow(() -> CleanUtil.cleanDirectBuffer(directBuffer));\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void cleanDirectBufferSwallowsUnsupportedHeapByteBufferCleanup() {\\n        ByteBuffer heapBuffer = ByteBuffer.allocate(32);\\n        heapBuffer.put((byte) 1);\\n        heapBuffer.flip();\\n\\n        assertDoesNotThrow(() -> CleanUtil.cleanDirectBuffer(heapBuffer));\\n    }\\n\\n    private static ByteBuffer newDirectBuffer() {\\n        ByteBuffer directBuffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(32);\\n        directBuffer.put((byte) 1);\\n        directBuffer.flip();\\n        return directBuffer;\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void restoreJavaVersion(String previousJavaVersion) {\\n        if (previousJavaVersion == null) {\\n            System.clearProperty(JAVA_VERSION_PROPERTY);\\n        } else {\\n            System.setProperty(JAVA_VERSION_PROPERTY, previousJavaVersion);\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 824, \"output\": 1951, \"cacheRead\": 47616, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 50391, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778276210074, \"responseId\": \"resp_01d3ce057da11f900169fe577362d8819d82d8808217f29de8\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_SnU8CQMdpfwBiCd8zMTmLodS|fc_01d3ce057da11f900169fe5788f8c8819db88a524e40769